<p>What is the length of the unmeasured side of the triangle? <fillin characters="20" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>5.26</li></ul></p><p>Because it does not matter which leg is a and which is b we call the missing leg x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{6.03}^{{2}}={8.00}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{36.3609}={64}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={64}-{36.3609}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={27.6391}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{x}^{{2}}}}=\sqrt{{{27.6391}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx{5.26}</m>.</p>
</solution>
